title: Business Development
tagsAndSkills: Sales strategy,Networking,Strategic partnerships,Maritime,Regulatory compliance,Market research,Revenue generation,Monitoring
jobDescription:
• ROYAL HASKONINGDHV is looking for Business Development for Maritime to join our dynamic team and embark on a rewarding career journey
  • Market Research: Conduct comprehensive research on the maritime industry, including market trends, competitors, regulations, and potential growth areas
  • Identifying Opportunities: Identify and evaluate potential business opportunities within the maritime sector, such as new markets, partnerships, or service offerings
  • Building Relationships: Cultivate and maintain relationships with key stakeholders, including shipping companies, port authorities, logistics providers, and government agencies
  • Strategic Partnerships: Develop strategic partnerships or alliances with relevant industry players to expand market reach or offer complementary services
  • Sales and Revenue Generation: Develop and implement sales strategies to acquire new clients, negotiate contracts, and drive revenue growth
  • Proposal Development: Create compelling proposals, bids, and presentations tailored to the needs of maritime clients or partners
  • Regulatory Compliance: Stay updated with maritime regulations, trade policies, and compliance standards affecting the industry
  • Networking and Representation: Attend industry events, conferences, and forums to network, represent the company, and explore business opportunities
  • Monitoring Industry Trends: Keep abreast of technological advancements, environmental concerns, and global economic trends affecting the maritime sector
  • Strategies:Diversification: Identify new market segments or services within the maritime industry to diversify offerings and minimize risk
  • Innovation: Embrace technological innovations like IoT, AI, and blockchain to enhance efficiency and offer innovative solutions
  • Customer-Centric Approach: Understand client needs and provide tailored solutions to address specific challenges they face
  • Sustainability Initiatives: Integrate sustainability practices into business offerings to align with industry and global environmental trends
